obs: No artigo tem uma foto de satélite, Expedição em Xavantino/ Cachimbo. The new road starts at Xavantina (14°40'S : 52°20'W), on the Rio das Mortes and passes northwards along the Serra do Roncador (probably the site of the ill-fated Fawcettexpedition). It is destined to pass through Cachimbo but at the time of these present studies had halted approximately 530 kilometres distant from Xavantina, at S~o Felix. From Xavantina, northwards, the predominant vegetation is the scrubby "cerrado," composed of sparse grasses and smaU, fire-tolerant tree species and palms. At the encampment, however, (kilometre 260, 12°49'S : 51°46'W) (Figs 1 and 2) there is a sudden transition into the "mata seca" or high dry forest which continues, almost uninterrupted, to merge with the Amazonian forests in the North.

Na zona sul, os bairros Lagoa Nova; Ponta Negra (conjunto e vila) e Conjuntos Cidade Satélite, Bancários e Vale do Pitimbu (Pitimbu). Na zona oeste nos bairros e localidades Guarapes, Planalto, Bom Pastor, Felipe Camarão e Cidade da Esperança em residências com animais no peridomicílio e na zona leste em residências nos bairros de Mãe Luiza e Rocas.
